			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Unless I did something very wrong, the splits in <em>The Curse of Possum Hollow</em> are clean.<br /><br />You use the $2006-$2005-$2005-$2006 write pattern for the scroll and whatever your particular mapper requires for the background pattern table change. The last two writes of the scroll pattern have to be within the first 64 pixels of horizontal blanking, as they set the fine horizontal scroll and reload the nametable VRAM address. The write to change the background pattern table can be slightly earlier, as the PPU never does anything with the 34th pattern table's tile.<br /><br />For more specific advice, please answer the following questions:<br /><br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>Status bar at top or bottom? </li><li>Does the playfield scroll vertically? </li><li>Which mapper? </li></ol></div>

