			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think most games with split glitches just timed their register writes badly, probably because testing builds back in the day wasn't as quick and easy as it is today (some developers reportedly had to burn the game to EPROM for each and every test!), so they didn't spend much time tweaking these splits. Guess you'll have to debug the games and see when in the scanline the critical writes are taking place, and see if you can hack the code to delay or anticipate those writes so they fall in the proper hblank window.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

